				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">cd_vision wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The video card he designed is pretty neat. I've been wanting to make a little PC for emulating games but connected to my TV.  It doesn't seem like the TV out on most video cards reproduce the original quite right. I would probably buy something like that if it were commercially made.</div>
<br />That's only suitable for new NES-like PC homebrew though using CHR RAM. If you want to play other games you'd have to give it more RAM and a FPGA to cover CHR bankswitching unless the card can be written at a speed of 12KiB/Vblank to emulate bankswitching.
<br />
<br />The reason video card output isn't good is because it's generally scaled to 480 lines and interlaced. If you have/get a 15 kHz RGB display, try the ArcadeVGA which can actually output native game resolutions.</div>

